                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d381">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Iddings</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Rome</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1904-02-17">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 17, 1904</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>(Mr. Iddings reports that the instructions to the American representatives at St.
                    Petersburg, Tokyo, and Peking, which were transmitted to him by the Department,
                    have been given to the foreign office and that the Italian representatives at
                    the above-named places have been instructed in the sense of the memorandum
                    inclosed in his No. 335.)</p>
            </div>
        </body>
